29/11/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police arrested 17 people on Tuesday (November 28th), including customs officials and businessmen, on suspicion of bribery, fraud, abuse of office, smuggling and other crimes.
Police chief Milorad Veljovic said the arrests occurred in six towns across the country, adding that the probe may extend at some point to senior officials in the Customs Directorate.
Damage done to the state budget may total several million euros, he said.
(Blic, Politika - 29/11/06;
Tanjug - 28/11/06)
